__construct.name: __construct
__construct.short_desc: Create a new Eloquent query builder instance.

find.name: find
find.short_desc: Find a model by its primary key.

findMany.name: findMany
findMany.short_desc: Find a model by its primary key.

findOrFail.name: findOrFail
findOrFail.short_desc: Find a model by its primary key or throw an exception.

first.name: first
first.short_desc: Execute the query and get the first result.

firstOrFail.name: firstOrFail
firstOrFail.short_desc: Execute the query and get the first result or throw an exception.

get.name: get
get.short_desc: Execute the query as a "select" statement.

pluck.name: pluck
pluck.short_desc: Pluck a single column from the database.

chunk.name: chunk
chunk.short_desc: Chunk the results of the query.

lists.name: lists
lists.short_desc: Get an array with the values of a given column.

paginate.name: paginate
paginate.short_desc: Get a paginator for the "select" statement.

update.name: update
update.short_desc: Update a record in the database.

increment.name: increment
increment.short_desc: Increment a column's value by a given amount.

decrement.name: decrement
decrement.short_desc: Decrement a column's value by a given amount.

delete.name: delete
delete.short_desc: Delete a record from the database.

forceDelete.name: forceDelete
forceDelete.short_desc: Force a delete on a set of soft deleted models.

withTrashed.name: withTrashed
withTrashed.short_desc: Include the soft deleted models in the results.

onlyTrashed.name: onlyTrashed
onlyTrashed.short_desc: Force the result set to only included soft deletes.

getModels.name: getModels
getModels.short_desc: Get the hydrated models without eager loading.

eagerLoadRelations.name: eagerLoadRelations
eagerLoadRelations.short_desc: Eager load the relationships for the models.

getRelation.name: getRelation
getRelation.short_desc: Get the relation instance for the given relation name.

has.name: has
has.short_desc: Add a relationship count condition to the query.

whereHas.name: whereHas
whereHas.short_desc: Add a relationship count condition to the query with where clauses.

orHas.name: orHas
orHas.short_desc: Add a relationship count condition to the query with an "or".

orWhereHas.name: orWhereHas
orWhereHas.short_desc: Add a relationship count condition to the query with where clauses and an "or".

with.name: with
with.short_desc: Set the relationships that should be eager loaded.

getQuery.name: getQuery
getQuery.short_desc: Get the underlying query builder instance.

setQuery.name: setQuery
setQuery.short_desc: Set the underlying query builder instance.

getEagerLoads.name: getEagerLoads
getEagerLoads.short_desc: Get the relationships being eagerly loaded.

setEagerLoads.name: setEagerLoads
setEagerLoads.short_desc: Set the relationships being eagerly loaded.

getModel.name: getModel
getModel.short_desc: Get the model instance being queried.

setModel.name: setModel
setModel.short_desc: Set a model instance for the model being queried.

__call.name: __call
__call.short_desc: Dynamically handle calls into the query instance.

__clone.name: __clone
__clone.short_desc: Force a clone of the underlying query builder when cloning.
